      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(duckduckgo): guard out-of-range numeric HTML entities",
        "body": "## Problem\n`decodeHtmlEntities` decodes numeric entities with `String.fromCodePoint(Number.parseInt(...))` without a range check, so an out-of-range entity such as `&#99999999;` or `&#x110000;` throws `RangeError` and makes the whole results page fail to parse (title/url/snippet all go through it).\n\n## Fix\nValidate the code point is within `0..0x10FFFF` and keep the original entity text otherwise.\n\n## Proof\nAdded a regression in `extensions/duckduckgo/src/ddg-search-provider.test.ts` covering decimal and hex out-of-range entities (no throw, text preserved) plus a valid supplementary-plane entity that still decodes — fails before, passes after. Pure unit test.\n",
        "branch": "fix/duckduckgo-entity-range",
